When an issue is resolved (eg. a bug is fixed), often the roll-out of this fix is different for each fix-for version.  For an unreleased version, perhaps nothing need be done - the fix will appear in the new release.  For already released versions, perhaps a patch is needed.  For a stable branch, perhaps regression testing is needed.  Each of these release processes needs to be assigned to someone and progress tracked.

